    """Tell me what you want and I will give it to you,"" said Alexander the Great to Diogenes. ""I don't need anything,"" the sage responded, ""but if you want to make me happy, stop blocking my sunlight."""
    "Love isn't always a ray of sunshine. That's what the older girls kept telling her when she said she had found the perfect man. She had thought this was simply bitter talk on their part since they had been unable to find true love like hers."
